title: A Narrative of the Life of Mrs. Mary Jemison
creator: James E. Seaver
description: LibriVox recording of A Narrative of the Life of Mrs. Mary Jemison, by James E. Seaver. Read by LibriVox volunteers. Mrs. Mary Jemison was taken by the Indians, in the year 1755, when only about twelve years of age, and has continued to reside amongst them to the present time. Containing an account of the murder of her father and his family; her sufferings; her marriage to two Indians; her troubles with her children; barbarities of the Indians in the French and Revolutionary Wars; the life of her last husband, and many historical facts never before published. (Summary by James Seaver) M4B audiobook of complete book For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
